  &lt;p id="4MnIPg"&gt;Puerto Rico &lt;a href="https://www.justicia.pr.gov/departamento-de-justicia-demanda-a-empresas-multinacionales-de-energia-y-petroquimica-para-recobrar-danos-ambientales-ocasionados-en-la-isla/"&gt;filed suit&lt;/a&gt; against fossil fuel companies this week, alleging that the oil and gas giants have misled the public about climate change and delayed a transition to clean energy. The suit seeks $1 billion in damages to help Puerto Rico defend itself against climate disasters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="jXVsgf"&gt;In a &lt;a href="https://climateintegrity.org/uploads/media/PR_complaint_filed_071524.pdf"&gt;complaint&lt;/a&gt; filed in San Juan yesterday, Puerto Rico’s Department of Justice says that the companies violated trade law by promoting fossil fuels without adequately warning about the dangers. The defendants include ExxonMobil, BP, Chevron, Shell, ConocoPhillips, and other energy companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="2cHMAw"&gt;It’s the latest in a &lt;a href="https://grist.org/accountability/big-oil-climate-lawsuits-trials-attribution-science-exxon/"&gt;slew of lawsuits&lt;/a&gt; attempting to hold fossil fuel companies accountable for the consequences of climate change. Greenhouse gas emissions from fossil...&lt;/p&gt;
